snippet: Iran has resumed shipping military equipment to Syria over Iraqi airspace, showing the limits of American influence in the region after the White House pressed Baghdad to close the corridor.
abstract: Senior American officials say that Iran has resumed shipping military equipment to Syria over Iraqi airspace in a new effort to bolster the embattled government of Pres Bashar al-Aassad; State Dept has not officially responded to questions about what efforts the United States has made to encourage the Iraqi government to stop the flights, which are seen as an illumination of the limits of American influence in the region.

byline.contributor: David D. Kirkpatrick contributed reporting from Beirut, Lebanon.

lead_paragraph: Iran has resumed shipping military equipment to Syria over Iraqi airspace, showing the limits of American influence in the region after the White House pressed Baghdad to close the corridor.
